  "prompt": "How can I become member of Mensa India?",
  "response": "Becoming a member of Mensa India involves several steps, primarily focused on demonstrating your high IQ. Here\u2019s a general outline of what you need to do:\n\n1. **Eligibility**: You must score within the top 2% of the population on an approved intelligence test.\n\n2. **Application Process**:\n   - **Take the Test**: Register for a Mensa-supervised IQ test. Mensa India conducts tests periodically in various cities. You can check the Mensa India website or contact them directly for test schedules and registration details.\n   - **Test Fee**: Pay any applicable test fees. The fees can vary depending on the test location and other factors.\n\n3. **Prepare for the Test**:\n   - You may choose to prepare by practicing sample IQ tests or puzzles, although intelligence tests typically measure innate cognitive abilities rather than learned knowledge.\n\n4. **Testing Day**:\n   - It is necessary to bring valid identification on the test day.\n   - Follow all test instructions carefully and complete the test within the given timeframe.\n\n5. **Results**:\n   - After the test, your scores will be evaluated. If you score within the top 2% of the population, you will receive an invitation to join Mensa India.\n\n6. **Membership Fee**:\n   - Upon receiving your invitation, you may need to pay a membership fee to officially join the organization. The fee can vary, so it\u2019s best to check with Mensa India for the exact details.\n\n7. **Membership Benefits**:\n   - As a Mensa member, you can participate in various intellectual and social activities, access Mensa-exclusive publications, attend special events, and connect with other high IQ individuals globally.\n\nFor the most accurate and updated information, you should visit the Mensa India website or contact their local office. They can provide specific details about upcoming tests, fees, and any other requirements or changes in the application process.",
